{"parse":{"title":"is it","pageid":3785703,"redirects":[],"wikitext":"{{also|isit}}\n==English==\n\n===Alternative forms===\n* {{alt|en|issit||Singapore}}\n* {{alt|en|izit||South Africa}}\n* {{alt|en|izzit}}\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|en|/(ˈ)ɪz ɪt/}}\n* {{audio|en|En-us-is it.ogg|a=US}}\n\n===Interjection===\n{{en-intj}}\n\n# {{&lit|en|is|it}}\n#: {{ux|en|- It's ten o'clock already.<br>- '''Is it'''?}}\n# {{lb|en|Canada|South Africa|Indian English|MLE|MTE}} [[really]]? [[is that so]]?\n#: {{ux|en|- I'm feeling tired.<br>- '''Is it'''?}}\n#* '''2007''', Dan le Sac vs. Scroobius Pip, \"Thou Shalt Always Kill\" on ''Angles''\n#*: Thou shalt not express your shock at the fact that Sharon got off with Brad at the club last night by saying \"'''is it'''?\"\n#* {{quote-book|en|date=2011-07-31|author=James Ashcroft|title=Making A Killing: The Explosive Story of a Hired Gun in Iraq|publisher=Random House|isbn=9780753547748|page=80\n|text='Everyone just calls me Ash.'<br/>{{'}}'''Izzit'''?' said Hendriks, and he fixed me with his cold grey eyes. Spartan at that time was unusual in that it would only take on ex-army South Africans.}}\n\n====Translations====\n{{trans-top}}\n* Spanish: {{t|es|[[será]]}}, {{t|es|[[será]] [[cierto]]}}, {{t|es|[[será]] [[verídico]] [[eso]]}}, {{t|es|[[será]] [[verífico]] [[aqueso]]}}, {{t+|es|qué va}}, {{t+|es|quia}}, {{t+|es|ca}}, {{t+|es|jum}} {{qualifier|Latin America}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n===Particle===\n{{en-head|pcl}}\n\n# {{lb|en|Singapore|Malaysia|Wales}} {{non-gloss|Final interrogative particle forming a [[tag question]].}}\n#: {{usex|en|You forgot, '''is it'''?}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=1994|author=Michael Chiang|title=Private Parts & Other Play Things|page=242\n|passage=You think you slang-slang a bit I scared, '''is it'''? Bloody fool!}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=2008|author=Nicholas Drayson|title=A Guide to the Birds of East Africa|page=187|passage=\"I mean what now - the bet is cancelled but they are both going to ask her, '''is it'''?\"}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=2012|author=w:Tan Twan Eng|title=w:The Garden of Evening Mists|isbn=1905802498|chapter=1|page=15|publisher=Hachette|passage=So short-''{{l|en|lah|id=authoritativeness}}'', the chopstick. For children '''is it'''?}}\n\n====Usage notes====\nIn contrast to the neutral {{m|en|or not}}, questions formed with ''is it'' expect an affirmative response.\n\n====Synonyms====\n*{{l|en|or not}}\n\n===Anagrams===\n* {{anagrams|en|a=iist|-itis|IIST|IITs|SITI|itis}}\n\n[[Category:Singlish]]\n[[Category:Manglish]]"}}